  <entry>
    <title>Lazy man&#39;s package of nationwide U.S. boundaries</title>
    <link href="http://haoliangyu.github.io/blog/2015/12/05/Lazy-man-s-package-of-U-S-boundaries/"/>
    <id>http://haoliangyu.github.io/blog/2015/12/05/Lazy-man-s-package-of-U-S-boundaries/</id>
    <published>2015-12-05T05:00:00.000Z</published>
    <updated>2016-01-24T05:00:00.000Z</updated>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;p&gt;I have been doing GIS work for quite a while and I do hate to download data from multiple sites every time. So I decide to collect those commonly geospatial data and make my own database. Of course, like all open-source people do, I’d love to share my work with you. The first release is the U.S. nationwide U.S. boundary. This dataset include &lt;strong&gt;nation&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;state&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;county&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;place&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;census block&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;census tract&lt;/strong&gt;. The source data come from U.S. Census Bureau and you can find the metadata &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/tiger-cart-boundary.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Multiple formats provided: &lt;strong&gt;shapefile&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;geojson&lt;/strong&gt;, and a &lt;strong&gt;postgis&lt;/strong&gt; database dump.&lt;/p&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
